<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The epithet of the specific name, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">petila</emphasis>
, is originated from the Latin word 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">petilus</emphasis>
. This name refers to the shape of pereopod 5 coxa and basis, and pereopods 6 and 7 basis, which are slenderer than those of other photid amphipods.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
