<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as head; without robust seta posteriodistally; 2nd article 2.0
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as 1st article; 3rd article 0.8
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as 2nd article; accessory flagellum uniarticulated, vestigial; flagellum 2.0
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as peduncle 3rd article, composed of nine articles (terminal article rudimentary).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Antenna 2 (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Exiliphotis petila sp. nov., holotype, NIBRIV 0000806532, male, 3.7 mm, Daegwantal-do Island, South Korea. A habitus B, C antenna 1 D antenna 2 E upper lip F lower lip G, H left mandible I right mandible. Scale bars: 0.05 mm (G-I), 0.1 mm (C, E, F), 0.2 mm (B, D), 0.5 mm (A)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.38511.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352713" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.38511.figure1">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
) 1.1
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as antenna 1; peduncle 4th article 0.7
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as 2nd article of antenna 1; 5th article as long as 4th article; flagellum 1.9
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as peduncle 5th article, composed of ten articles (terminal article rudimentary).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Upper lip (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Exiliphotis petila sp. nov., holotype, NIBRIV 0000806532, male, 3.7 mm, Daegwantal-do Island, South Korea. A habitus B, C antenna 1 D antenna 2 E upper lip F lower lip G, H left mandible I right mandible. Scale bars: 0.05 mm (G-I), 0.1 mm (C, E, F), 0.2 mm (B, D), 0.5 mm (A)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.38511.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352713" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.38511.figure1">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
) convex anteriorly, with notch in the middle, covered with minute setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Lower lip (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Exiliphotis petila sp. nov., holotype, NIBRIV 0000806532, male, 3.7 mm, Daegwantal-do Island, South Korea. A habitus B, C antenna 1 D antenna 2 E upper lip F lower lip G, H left mandible I right mandible. Scale bars: 0.05 mm (G-I), 0.1 mm (C, E, F), 0.2 mm (B, D), 0.5 mm (A)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.38511.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352713" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.38511.figure1">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
) inner lobe subovoid, outer lobe apex rounded, covered with minute setae; mandibular process well developed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Mandibles (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Exiliphotis petila sp. nov., holotype, NIBRIV 0000806532, male, 3.7 mm, Daegwantal-do Island, South Korea. A habitus B, C antenna 1 D antenna 2 E upper lip F lower lip G, H left mandible I right mandible. Scale bars: 0.05 mm (G-I), 0.1 mm (C, E, F), 0.2 mm (B, D), 0.5 mm (A)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.38511.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352713" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.38511.figure1">
Fig. 1
<normalizedToken originalValue="G–I">G-I</normalizedToken>
</figureCitation>
) with 1/2 and 4-dentate incisor, 4-dentate lacinia mobilis, and four raker setae on left mandible; with 5-dentate incisor, minutely dentate lacinia mobilis, and three raker setae on right mandible; molar well developed, triturative, with seven setae along the distal margin of right mandible; palp asymmetrical, composed of three articles, 3rd article distally rounded, 0.8
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as 2nd article, with setae extending along most of posteriodistal margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Maxilla 1 (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Exiliphotis petila sp. nov., holotype, NIBRIV 0000806532, male, 3.7 mm, Daegwantal-do Island, South Korea. A maxilla 1 B maxilla 2 C maxilliped D gnathopod 1 E, F gnathopod 2 G pereopod 3. Scale bars: 0.05 mm (A, B), 0.1 mm (C-G)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.38511.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352714" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.38511.figure2">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
) inner lobe small, without seta; outer lobe with ten dentate setae on apical margin; palp biarticulated, 2nd article slightly dilated distally, with five dentate setae apically and five simple setae subapically.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.886.38511.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352714" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 2" startId="F2">
