<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Maxilla 2 (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Exiliphotis petila sp. nov., holotype, NIBRIV 0000806532, male, 3.7 mm, Daegwantal-do Island, South Korea. A maxilla 1 B maxilla 2 C maxilliped D gnathopod 1 E, F gnathopod 2 G pereopod 3. Scale bars: 0.05 mm (A, B), 0.1 mm (C-G)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.38511.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352714" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.38511.figure2">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
) inner lobe with an oblique row of five weakly plumose setae on surface; outer lobe lager than inner lobe, expanded distally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Maxilliped (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Exiliphotis petila sp. nov., holotype, NIBRIV 0000806532, male, 3.7 mm, Daegwantal-do Island, South Korea. A maxilla 1 B maxilla 2 C maxilliped D gnathopod 1 E, F gnathopod 2 G pereopod 3. Scale bars: 0.05 mm (A, B), 0.1 mm (C-G)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.38511.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352714" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.38511.figure2">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
) inner lobe subrectangular, with three nodular setae apically and one medial nodular seta subdistally; outer lobe semiovoid, apex beyond half of 2nd palp article, lined with ten stout setae on medial to apical margins; palp composed of four articles, 3rd article a little expanded distally, half as long as 2nd article, 4th article 0.6
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as 3rd article, with elongate seta apically (1.1
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as 4th article).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Gnathopod 1 (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Exiliphotis petila sp. nov., holotype, NIBRIV 0000806532, male, 3.7 mm, Daegwantal-do Island, South Korea. A maxilla 1 B maxilla 2 C maxilliped D gnathopod 1 E, F gnathopod 2 G pereopod 3. Scale bars: 0.05 mm (A, B), 0.1 mm (C-G)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.38511.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352714" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.38511.figure2">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
) coxa subtrapezoidal, 0.7
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as wide as long, slightly produced anterioventrally; basis subtrapezoidal, anterior margin distal lobe weakly developed, with four elongate setae in the middle, posterior margin convex subproximally, with seven setae; carpus broad, 2.0
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide, 0.8
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as basis, with carpal lobe broad and blunt; propodus as long and as wide as carpus, anterior margin evenly rounded, with five oblique rows of elongate setae submarginally, posterior margin more convex than anterior margin, free form carpal lobe proximally, palmar margin convex, finely serrated on distal 3/4 margin, not defined distinctively, with one robust seta medially at 1/3 length distally; dactylus elongate, 0.8
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as propodus, inner margin finely serrated, with four teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Gnathopod 2 (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Exiliphotis petila sp. nov., holotype, NIBRIV 0000806532, male, 3.7 mm, Daegwantal-do Island, South Korea. A maxilla 1 B maxilla 2 C maxilliped D gnathopod 1 E, F gnathopod 2 G pereopod 3. Scale bars: 0.05 mm (A, B), 0.1 mm (C-G)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.38511.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352714" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.38511.figure2">Fig. 2E, F</figureCitation>
) subequal to gnathopod 1; coxa subtrapezoidal, 1.1
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as wide as that of gnathopod 1, 0.7
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as wide as long, rounded ventrally, not produced anterioventrally; coxal gill subovoid, 0.9
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as coxa; basis similar to that of gnathopod 1, without setae on anterior margin; carpus 0.7
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as basis and that of gnathopod 1, carpal lobe also shorter than that of gnathopod 1, blunt posteriorly; propodus as long as basis, 1.6
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as carpus, anterior margin evenly rounded, posterior margin convex, not free from carpal lobe proximally, finely serrated on distal half margin, palmar margin oblique, strongly bisinuated, finely serrated, defined by one robust seta medially; dactylus 0.7
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as propodus, exceeding palm, inner margin finely serrated, with three teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Pereopod 3 (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Exiliphotis petila sp. nov., holotype, NIBRIV 0000806532, male, 3.7 mm, Daegwantal-do Island, South Korea. A maxilla 1 B maxilla 2 C maxilliped D gnathopod 1 E, F gnathopod 2 G pereopod 3. Scale bars: 0.05 mm (A, B), 0.1 mm (C-G)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.38511.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352714" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.38511.figure2">Fig. 2G</figureCitation>
) coxa as wide but 0.9
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as that of gnathopod 2, rounded ventrally, weakly produced anterioventrally, coxal gill subovoid, 1.1
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
